'''Ammonium malate''' is a [[Compound (chemistry)|compound]] with formula NH<sub>4</sub>(C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>O(COO)<sub>2</sub>). It is the [[ammonium]] [[salt (chemistry)|salt]] of [[malic acid]]. It is used as a [[food additive]] and has the [[E number]] E349.
There is a recommendation to avoid this food additive.<ref name=FOOD1>{{cite web|url= https://www.dangersalimentaires.com/en/2011/01/les-additifs-alimentaires/ |title=Food additives |publisher=Food Alerts| date=16 January 2011 |quote= Ammonium malate E349: Avoid|accessdate=18 November 2017}}</ref>
