'''Wet infrastructure''' is the spectrum of water-related projects relating to water supply, treatment and storage, water resource management, flood management, coastal restoration, [[hydropower]] and [[renewable energy]] facilities.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mwhglobal.com/MWHGlobal/Wet_Infrastructure.html|title=Integrated Water Resources Management - MWH Global|website=Mwhglobal.com|accessdate=14 October 2017}}</ref> Common examples of wet infrastructure include new construction as well as renovations and maintenance of locks, weirs, storm-surge barriers, guiding structures, pumping plants, [[culverts]], bridges, controlling systems, operating systems, and tunnel installations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rijkswaterstaat.nl/rws/bwd/home/www/cgi-bin/index.cgi?site=10&doc=1969|title=The Civil Engineering Division of the Netherlands|website=Rijkswaterstaat.nl|accessdate=14 October 2017}}</ref>
